# ELECT-MT â€” Automated Image Processing (Python + OpenCV)

This project automatically processes images dropped into an `input/` directory and writes processed outputs to `output/`.

## Features
- Automatically detects image files (watch mode)
- Batch mode to process all images in `input/`
- Applies multiple OpenCV techniques (grayscale, edge detection, invert)
- CI pipeline via GitHub Actions runs `pytest` on every push/PR

## Quick Start

### 1) Create a virtual environment

Windows (PowerShell):
```powershell
python -m venv .venv
.\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
```

### 2) Install dependencies
```powershell
pip install -r requirements.txt
pip install -e .
```

### 3) Put images into `input/`
Supported extensions: `.png`, `.jpg`, `.jpeg`, `.bmp`, `.tif`, `.tiff`

### 4) Run batch processing
```powershell
elect-mt batch --input input --output output
```

### 5) Run watch processing
```powershell
elect-mt watch --input input --output output
```

## Output naming
For an input file `cat.jpg`, outputs are written as:
- `cat_gray.png`
- `cat_edges.png`
- `cat_invert.png`

## Testing
```powershell
pytest
```
